ut shows evidence for the opposite behavior. We\nconclude that the RV signal of active stars does not vanish at longer\nwavelength but sensitively depends on the combination of spot temperature and\nmagnetic field; in active low-mass stars, it is even likely to grow with\nwavelength.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Jan 2013 12:40:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
